gner focusing on international development. But in 2008 she burnt out as an activist and introvert and wanted to find an effective way of campaigning that fitted her skills and ethics and personality. She set up the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://craftivist-collective.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Craftivist Collective</a>&nbsp;social enterprise in 2009 after people wanted to join in her new form of activism. Now there are craftivists around the world who take part in social change using handicrafts.</p><p>Corbett won the Sheila McKechnie award for Economic Justice campaigner of the Year 2016. Craftivist Collective won an Innovation Award from Care2 Impact Award 2016. She works with charities, arts institutions, universities and has exhibited her solo exhibition, &quot;Gentle Protest,&quot; in Stockholm, Helsinki and London.&nbsp;She lives in East London and works worldwide.</p>"}],"url":"https://www.ted.com/talks/sarah_corbett_activism_needs_introverts","viewed_count":1064567,"talks":[{"recommendations":{"status":"approved","headline":"Sarah Corbett recommends","blurb":"Extra resources, curated by Sarah Corbett","start_at":null,"end_at":null,"published":true,"eyebrow":"","type":"recommendation","rec_lists":[{"title":"","description":"","rec_items":[{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*Strength to Love*","blurb":"I re-read this collection of sermons regularly for his wisdom on how to love those who are causing harm in the world, how to work with people without losing your head or your principles ,and how to focus on the vision of a better world while protesting to end current harm. There are frequent references to philosophers, to other religions and to honest struggles he himself had. This book continues to shape my activism and life. ","note":"Martin Luther King Jr.\r\nFortress Press, 2010","link_url":"https://www.amazon.com/Strength-Love-Martin-Luther-King/dp/0800697405/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position"